The paper deals with the construction of codes based on spatially coupled low-density parity-check (SC-LDPC) codes, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and network coding (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the improved decoding properties of the constructed ensembles, which is relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the use of protographs, which are commonly used in coding theory (cs.CC).
